Glyph of Warding

This object will create a glyph of warding at its location in the game. There are a couple of Variables you can set on this object to change the glyphs behavior.

int X2_PLC_GLYPH_CASTER_LEVEL - The caster level used for the spellscript

int X2_PLC_GLYPH_CASTER_METAMAGIC - Metamagic conditions like with (GetMetaMagicFeat());

int X2_PLC_GLYPH_SPELL - The ID of the spell to run when someone triggers the glyph (default = 764, fireball = 58, basically most spells from spells.2da works, some may not)

int  X2_PLC_GLYPH_PERMANENT - if set to 1 the glyph will not have a duration based on the caster level but instead remain until triggered.

int X2_PLC_GLYPH_CHARGES - you can set the number of times the glyph will fire until destroyed here. -1 means permanent, 0 means 1 time, 1 means 2 times, etc... Player created glyphs always last only one time/
